commit.message: Remove __reduce__ as it was only needed because of __new__.
Fix reference in docs and some minor project issues.
Replace the `__new__` trick with slightly more boiler plate. This should make the class more predictable to users.
Rework test to not use internals.
Try to figure out where pytest has problems with tblib tracebacks.
Turns out stdlib also have lots of .to_stuff ... well, just alias everything. Yes, I forget things.
Prevent as_traceback mutating the object (turns out exec will add builtins to the globals). Add some tests that illustrate the bug.
Rename Traceback.to_dict to as_dict to be consistent with other api (to_dict still kept as alias for now). This is also consistent with stdlib (lots of stuff use .as_something).
Type check the parameters of install; allow using it as a decorator
